info.title: SPENDiD
info.description: Demographically validated spending behavior models, automated user budget creation, and alternative metrics for cash-flow or budget health scoring. SPENDiD brings an addictively sticky user-experience component to any consumer facing financial wellness, digital banking, or other PFM platform.
info.x-long-description:
SPENDiD is a REST API that uses proprietary demographic/peer modeling to help developers offer their application end-user with addictively simple automated budget creation and refinement, cash-flow health scoring, secondary lending metrics, and marketing data insights by connecting to one or all three of SPENDiD's easy to use end-points.  

Our API platform helps you build powerful cutting edge FinTech apps in radically less time - which of course means lower cost and earlier revenue for you and your firm. SPENDiD offers the first of its kind off-the-shelf functionality to generate household/consumer demographic models, personalized budgets, plus financial health and secondary lending scores. Plus, SPENDiD can offer valuable marketing data by helping highlight the end-user's spending behaviors which may indicate opportunities for focused outreach by marketers, lenders, advisors, etc...

PERSONALIZED SPENDING BEHAVIOR INSIGHTS
SPENDiD has harnessed the powerful application of properly sourced “crowd-wisdom” theory and relative spending behavior. Truly personalized marketing to a consumer's "hot-buttons" is now easier than ever. 

SIMPLE PEER-GUIDED BUDGETING
You can now bring the customer or employee a giant step closer to autonomous finance using simple, peer guided budget creation and refinement. Powered by a simple Q&A process flow, there actually is a short-cut to financial success!

USEFUL SPENDiD SCORING METRICS
SPENDiD offers a unique and addictive scoring metric indicating to the end-user or SPENDiD client the relative strength of the User's cash flow health. These scores can be presented in numeric terms, or in a traditional A-F grading scale, or both. 

You'll find comprehensive guides on our developer site at https://docs.spendid.io/ and documentation to help you start working with our services quickly, as well as support if you ever need it.

Please be sure to also visit our landing site at https://www.spendid.io/
